NEW CD-ROM DATABASES FROM DIALOG
 
Dialog Information Services, Inc. has announced six new CD-ROM
products: (1) OnDisc AEROSPACE DATABASE, which provides
international coverage of scientific and technical literature
related to aerospace engineering (available Fall 1990); (2)
OnDisc Ei CHEMDISC, which covers technology issues for chemical
engineers (available now); (3) OnDisc KIRK-OTHMER, which contains
the full-text of the third edition of the Kirk-Othmer
Encyclopedia of Chemical Technology (available summer 1990); (4)
OnDisc L.A. Times, which provides the full-text  of all three
daily versions of the Los Angeles Times plus stories unique to
the Orange County, San Diego, Chatsworth, and Ventura editions
(available late summer 1990); (5) OnDisc METADEX COLLECTION,
which combines the METADEX, MATERIALS BUSINESS FILE, and
ENGINEERED MATERIALS ABSTRACTS databases to cover the areas of
metals, polymers, and ceramics (available Fall 1990); and (6)
OnDisc SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS, which provides the full-text of the
San Jose Mercury News (available Fall 1990).
 
For more information contact: Marketing Department, Dialog
Information Services, Inc., 3460 Hillview Avenue, Palo Alto, CA
94304 (800) 334-2564.
 
 
GEAC SYSTEM WILL BE LINKED TO CD-ROM OPAC
 
Geac Computer Corporation and the Massachusetts Institute of
Technology Libraries have announced a cooperative project to link
MIT's Geac Series 8000 system with microcomputer-based
Marcive/PAC CD-ROM online catalogs.  This interface will permit
bibliographic and item status information to be downloaded from
the Geac system to the Marcive CD-ROM OPAC units.  The software
modules that will be developed will also be available for use
with Geac Series 9000 systems.
 
